cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses spreadsheet research aimed at reducing error-proneness and improving spreadsheet quality. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper analyzes how users interact with spreadsheets and decision support information presented through charts, pivot tables, and array formulas. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper deals with data management and decision-making based on information from spreadsheets. 
- cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are less likely categories as they are not directly related to the topic of the paper.
